<h2>A Medieval Pilgrimage</h2>

<dl>
<dt>A Medieval Pilgrimage</dt>
<dd>A Musical Tour of the Middle Ages<br>
AROW - American Recorder Orchestra of the West - Richard Geisler<br>
<i>The Village &amp; Early Music Society  (no number)</i> [CD]</dd>
</dl>

<h3>Contents:</h3>
<p><ol>
<li>O rubor sanguinis (Hildegard von Bingen, 1098-1179)</li>
<li>Magnus Liber Organi (Leoninus, 1135-c1201)</li>
<li>Palastinalied (Walter von der Vogelweide, c.1170-1230)</li>
<li>Sederunt Principes (Perotin, c.1155-c1205)</li>
<li>Gram piant' agli ochi (Francesco Landini, 1325-1397)</li>
<li>Au tem Pascor (Jehans Erars, c.1200-c1259)</li>
<li>Trotto (Anon., Italy, 13th cent.)</li>
<li>Septi&egrave;me estampie real (France, 13th cent.)</li>
<li>La Rotta (Anon., Italy, 14th cent.)</li>
<li>Ma fin (Guillaume de Machaut, c.1300-1377)</li>
<li>Ha! Fortune (Machaut)</li>
<li>Je suis aussi (Machaut)</li>
<li>Lamentio sacrae (Guillaume Dufay, c.1400-1474)</li>
<li>Rose, liz printemps (Machaut)</li>
<li>Bache bene venie (Anon., Carmina Burana, Germany, 13th cent.)</li>
<li>Fanfare: Vive le Roy (Josquin des Pres, c.1440-1521)</li>
<li>Sanctus (Roi Henri IV)</li>
<li>Medieval Medley:<br>
Amours cent mille (Jehan l'Escurel, 13th cent.)<br>
Is milde lomb (England, 13th cent.)</li>
<li>O rosa bella (John Dunstable, c1390-1453)</li>
<li>Ja nuns hons pris (Richard the Lionhearted)</li>
<li>If Love Now Reigned (Henry VIII, 1491-1547)</li>
<li>Byrd one brere (Anon., England, 13th cent.)</li>
<li>Estampie (Anon., England, 14th cent.)</li>
<li>A la guerra (Anon., Spain, 16th cent.)</li>
<li>A Virgen (Cantiga de Santa Maria 322, Alfonso X, 1221-1284)</li>
<li>Polorum Regina (Anon., Llibre Vermell, Spain, 14th cent.)</li>
<li>Santa Maria amar (CSM 7)</li>
<li>Ave Maria (Francisco Guerrero, 1528-1599)</li>
<li>Corten espadas afiladas (Anon., Spain, 16th cent.)</li>
</ol></p>

<p><b>Playing time:</b> 60' 36"
</p>

